      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is there a good reason to only allow SECBIT_KEEP_CAPS to remain off if set_ambient_caps is set? Note that this is set_ambient_caps in the inner minijail, so it doesn\u0027t even make sense if you don\u0027t plan on having further child processes?\n\nIf we were to allow SECBIT_KEEP_CAPS to remain off unconditionally if it\u0027s locked already, would we lose anything? It seems there isn\u0027t anything bad that can happen. If the bit is off, we might lose capabilities on setuid(), but that\u0027ll fail closed. On the other hand, if we loosened the logic here, we\u0027d make it simpler to run nested minijails (the various -B 0x20 flags to minijail0 invocations we have right now in the code to keep SECBIT_KEEP_CAPS unlock as a workaround would no longer be necessary).",
